Amendment No. 2 to HB2275
Behn
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2207* House Bill No. 2275
by deleting subsection (j) and substituting instead the following:
(j) Except as provided in this subsection (j), the advisory board's recommended
guidelines must be made available to the public on the department of commerce and
insurance's website. The advisory board may designate specific portions of the
guidelines that contain detailed security vulnerability information as restricted from public
view, making such portions available only to governmental entities. Any restricted
designation must be documented with a specific written justification. The existence of
restricted portions and the general subject matter thereof shall be disclosed publicly.
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting subsection (f) and substituting instead the following:
(f) Except as provided in this subsection (f), advisory board meetings are subject
to the open meetings laws compiled in title 8, chapter 44. The advisory board may hold
closed sessions limited to discussion of specific security vulnerabilities or tactical
information that would compromise school safety if publicly disclosed; provided, that the
board documents the basis for closing any portion of a meeting and that the general
substance of all meetings is made available in public minutes within thirty (30) days.
